  .guide
    .content
      h2 Production
      p North Dakota statute specifies the flag and eagle’s dimensions in feet and inches.
      p It uses an unusual proportion of 26:33 (a hoist of 4 feet, 4 inches and a fly of 5 feet, 6 inches), but it is often produced with a 3:5 proportion.
      p The eagle should be 3 feet, 4 inches wing to wing and 1 foot, 10 inches from head to olive branch.
      p The flag can have an optional border of knotted yellow fringe 2 and 1/2 inches wide.
    .visual
      img(src='/assets/images/flag-north-dakota-dimensions.svg')

